# skill-consolidation-nuance-audit-workflow — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-07)

- **Changed by**: two-pass audit of 50-bundle consolidation
- **Verification**: verified-ci

### What changed

- Added the **audit-EVERY-bundle** rule: do not size-threshold the audit. Pass 1 (biggest 13
  bundles only) declared the merges sound, but pass 2 over the 37 mid-size bundles found 22 of 36
  with genuine body-not-surfaced losses (~60% of real losses lived in the skipped mid-size merges).
- Added the **materiality bar** definition: a LOST finding requires a distinctive
  command/flag/named-failure-mode/unique-lesson that is absent from the canonical body AND would
  change reader action; generalization, dedup, and deliberate scope-narrowing are NOT losses;
  everything is recoverable from the `.history` `## Superseded from` blocks.
- Refined the **swarm shape**: one read-only Explore agent per bundle (≤5 per wave) reading
  canonical + `.history` and emitting per-skill OK/LOST plus a VERDICT line; one general-purpose
  amend agent per bundle with a material loss; clean bundles get no PR. Reconciled with the prior
  Haiku-per-pair / Sonnet-per-bundle wording.
- Added the **common-loss-shapes checklist** (exception/type mapping tables, specific CLI flags,
  named failure modes with reproductions, dropped "permanent fix" paths, collapsed pipeline how-tos,
  ruff/lint rule-specific recipes, "green CI doesn't certify X" cautions).
- Added the **pre-commit run-once-and-re-stage** helper note (EOF-fixer aborts the first commit
  unless pre-run + re-staged).
- Added 4 new Failed-Attempts rows and a new Verified On row for the pass-2 audit.

### Why

- The first audit pass was over-confident: restricting coverage to the largest bundles missed the
  majority of the genuine losses. Capturing the audit-every-bundle rule, the materiality bar, and
  the refined swarm shape prevents the next consolidation audit from repeating the under-coverage.

## v1.0.0

- Initial version: parallel swarm workflow for detecting and restoring knowledge lost when
  individual skill files are bulk-consolidated into larger bundle files. Phase 0 pre-audit check,
  Phase 1 parallel audit swarm, Phase 2 triage, Phase 3 amendment swarm, Phase 4 PR creation with
  auto-merge; conservative flagging criteria and audit output schema.
